Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.32,0:00:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has warned us that we’re living \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.73,0:00:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in “critical times hard to deal with.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.60,0:00:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jesus foretold that in the last days \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.80,0:00:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,there would be great “earthquakes \Nin one place after another” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.94,0:00:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and other “fearful sights.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.81,0:00:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of us either have or will be affected \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.72,0:00:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by some form of natural disaster.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.85,0:00:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If this happens, how can we be prepared?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.43,0:00:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,First, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.43,0:00:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we can prepare spiritually by maintaining \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.16,0:00:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a close relationship with Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.80,0:00:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He is “the God of all comfort,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.67,0:00:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and he can comfort us \Nin times of tribulation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.87,0:00:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How does he do this?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.34,0:01:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We do not expect divine intervention. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.54,0:01:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we pray during times of distress, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.78,0:01:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,his powerful holy spirit \Ncan bring Bible passages \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.25,0:01:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,back to mind to comfort us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.12,0:01:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.13,0:01:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we can take practical steps, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.06,0:01:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps preparing an emergency kit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.23,0:01:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Our kit could contain \Nthe following items if possible: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.07,0:01:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,first-aid supplies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.62,0:01:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,bottled water, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.67,0:01:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and nonperishable food.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.10,0:01:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, we shouldn’t forget \Nto update the elders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.34,0:01:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with our latest contact information. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.89,0:01:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don’t do so, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.89,0:01:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,valuable time could be lost in a disaster.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.93,0:01:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, \Nduring a Family Worship evening, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.70,0:01:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,our family could review \Nthe types of disasters that might happen \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.57,0:02:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and what could be done in each situation\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.07,0:02:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,—such as where we meet, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.23,0:02:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,how we contact the elders, and so forth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.55,0:02:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And third, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.55,0:02:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we can help others \Nwhen they’re experiencing a disaster, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.62,0:02:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing they’d do the same for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.89,0:02:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we do this? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.53,0:02:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,By offering prayers in their behalf, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.55,0:02:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,by volunteering to assist \Nwith disaster relief efforts, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.90,0:02:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and by contributing donations \Nto the worldwide work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.74,0:02:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we can’t avoid all natural disasters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.85,0:02:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we prepare spiritually, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.27,0:02:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,practically, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.27,0:02:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and help others currently affected, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.42,0:02:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we can take comfort in knowing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.75,0:02:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that in Jehovah’s eyes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.82,0:02:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we are prepared.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.63,0:03:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That was great, practical advice \Nfor all of us to take to heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.46,0:03:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are some things \Nwe can do to help our local congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.33,0:03:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s turn briefly \Nto interview Brother Bram Siegel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.07,0:03:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,who’s with \Nthe Coordinators’ Committee Office.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.17,0:03:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Bram, how can all of us cooperate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.78,0:03:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,with the congregation arrangement \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.87,0:03:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,when a disaster hits?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.15,0:03:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately after a disaster occurs, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.12,0:03:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,each field service group overseer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.12,0:03:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,will contact everyone in his group \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.12,0:03:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to make sure that all are accounted for \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.12,0:03:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and to see if anyone needs assistance. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.43,0:03:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So each of us \Nshould make sure to give the elders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.53,0:03:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,our up-to-date contact information. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.06,0:03:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That way they can reach us \Nwhen something happens.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.10,0:03:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a very important reminder\N—good point! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.24,0:03:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if my area \Nwas not hit by the disaster \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.48,0:03:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but an adjacent town or city was? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.91,0:03:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I just travel there on my own to help, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.98,0:03:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,or what should I do?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.58,0:03:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We really appreciate \Nthe beautiful spirit the brotherhood shows \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.45,0:03:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes to providing disaster relief. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.06,0:04:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, the best time \Nto make yourself available to help \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.43,0:04:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is right now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.26,0:04:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,before a disaster occurs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.23,0:04:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Just ask your local elders \Nfor an application. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.00,0:04:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, when there’s a need \Nto provide disaster relief, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.83,0:04:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the branch office will know \Nthat you’re willing and ready to assist.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.01,0:04:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, Bram, \Nfor those important reminders.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.81,0:04:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N
